SIMPLE: mendacious
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mendacious
<hw>Men*da"cious</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>mendax</ets>, <ets>-acis</ets>, lying, cf. <ets>mentiri</ets> to
lie.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Given to deception or falsehood; lying;
<as>as, a <ex>mendacious</ex> person</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>False; counterfeit; containing falsehood; <as>as, a
<ex>mendacious</ex> statement</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Men*da"cious*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Men*da"cious*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mendacity</ent>⟦br⟧
